    <h3 id="usage">Usage</h3>

    <h4>Browser Extensions</h4>

    <p>
      <a href="https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/hn-reader/emgghjnnkkopedbjfajejpkidaiedhlf" target="_blank">
        Available at the Chrome Web Store
      </a>
    </p>

    <p>
      This app is designed to be used as a browser extension. Whenever you visit
      Hacker News, HN Reader will seamlessly take over and enhance your reading
      experience.
    </p>

    <p>
      The browser extension maintains 100% URL-compatibility with the original
      Hacker News site, so when you post a link into your company chat or visit
      a HN link from Twitter, everything would Just Work™.
    </p>

    <h4>Web App</h4>

    <p>
      This app can also be used as a <a href="https://chancancode.github.io/hn-reader/" target="_blank">stand-alone web app</a>.
      In fact, you are already <em>inside</em> the app! Head over to the
      {{link-to "front page" "stories" (query-params filter="front-page")}}
      and start reading!
    </p>

    <p>
      The app is fully responsive, so it is great for reading HN on your phone
      and tablets too.
    </p>

    <p>
      (Note: not all features are available on the web version)
    </p>
